517.name: Are you advertising a Fridge-freezer or an item of furniture..?
517.description:
.please read on .....for some Helpful Information.

Please include the dimensions for Fridges, Fridge Freezers and also items of furniture
The measurements matter to people who have a gap of a specific width into which the appliance must fit or an alcove into which a piece of furniture must fit....

If you're advertising a Fridge-Freezer (or an under counter Freezer or Fridge) - or any item of furniture - PLEASE REMEMBER TO INCLUDE THE DIMENSIONS - H, W and D.
A 60cm wide appliance will not fit into a 56 cm gap between units - nor even a 60cm gap.
Also many people only want, or need, a narrow F/F 50cm width or less ...due to shortage of space or the width of the gap between units.

Sometimes, when I've asked for more details, dimensions, Model number, and more pics (besides the solitary ONE posted) ... the seller either can't be bothered, or is just not interested in helping.. Often they don't even have a measuring tape...I ask you!!

Also, it is REALLY USEFUL to be able to see several pics of the item - including the inside layout of a Fridge (number of shelf positions) and to see whether or not the doors are reversible and also to compare with a current appliance.

Hoping the Gumtree Community will find this information and advice helpful.
